git checkout tag:

- jumps to the given tag.
- cmd: 
        git checkout v1.1

    -> HEAD now will be at the commit with tag v1.1.
    -> if we do any changes in file or add new file and do 'git add' and 'git commit', a different
       timeline of new commits will be created on a HEAD detached branch and things could get messy.
    -> to get back on the recent commit in main branch, simply do 'git checkout main'.
    -> (see git_checkout_TagCommitHEAD.png)

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________

git checkout commit:

- jumps to the given commit.
- cmd:
        git checkout 59df737

    -> HEAD now will be at the commit 59df737
    -> similar as 'git checkout tag'